# Per-finding exclusions for gitleaks. Each line is a fingerprint
# `<commit>:<file>:<rule>:<line>`. Used to silence false positives
# already in the immutable git history without forcing a rewrite.
#
# The HTML-REPORT smoke-test heredoc shipped a literal placeholder
# `api_key = "0123456789abcdef"` in 0.5.23 docs (commit 99bab44).
# Gitleaks treats any 16-char hex string under `api_key` as a leaked
# credential. The value is documentation-only, never deployed, but
# the historical commits cannot be rewritten without force-push to
# main. Subsequent commits replace the literal with a runtime-
# generated `$(openssl rand -hex 16)` placeholder so future scans of
# the working tree stay clean.
